def: Easy to be acquainted with; affable. [Obs.] Rom. of R.
A large, pearly, spiral, marine shell (Turbo margaritaceus),from the Pacific Islands. It is used as an ornament.
One engaged in warfare; a military man; a soldier; a warrior.
A small beaklike process or extension of some part; a smallrostrum; as, the rostellum of the stigma of violets, or of theoperculum of many mosses; the rostellum on the head of a tapeworm.

To drive or eject in a stream out of a narrow pipe or orifice;as, to squirt water.The hard-featured miscreant coolly rolled his tobacco in his cheek,and squirted the juice into the fire grate. Sir W. Scott.Squirting cucumber. (Bot.) See Ecballium.
To wall in; to inclose. [Obs.] Ford.
To remove a bar or bars from; to unbolt; to open; as, to unbara gate. Heber.
Having two heads on one body; double-headed.
The influenza or epidemic catarrh. Dunglison.
Making a harsh noise; blaring. "Braying trumpets." Shak.
